  "directive_events": [
    {
      "at": "2026-06-26T23:07:40.328951Z",
      "owner_directive": "Authorized: fix the global Stop so cancelling a workflow terminates every external process an app block launched (PTY agents and external GUI apps such as Fiji), not just the worker.",
      "reason": "Owner explicitly authorized admin-approved:core-change for bug 6 (global Stop must terminate every external process an app block launched: PTY agents and external GUI apps like Fiji). Fix touches protected engine/scheduler and app-block runtime."
    },
    {
      "at": "2026-06-26T23:21:30.622225Z",
      "owner_directive": "Bug 6: only make Stop responsive (no external-process kill). Bug 4 also: small->fullscreen resize must make the agent TUI redraw to fill the enlarged PTY.",
      "reason": "Owner narrowed bug 6: do NOT kill external processes; only fix the post-Stop unresponsiveness (UI hangs on the worker terminate grace period). Fix is frontend-only optimistic feedback - no protected engine/blocks change. The previously authorized admin-approved:core-change is therefore no longer needed for this PR. Owner also extended bug 4: resizing a PTY from small to fullscreen grows the PTY but the TUI content stays small (resize/refit not propagating)."
    },
    {
      "at": "2026-06-27T00:16:54.853501Z",
      "owner_directive": "A: spawn the agent PTY with the prompt as a CLI argument instead of typing it in. B: fix CompletionWatcher so a stale leftover output file no longer completes the block immediately.",
      "reason": "Owner authorized core-change to fix AI block lifecycle: (A) deliver the prompt as a spawn argv argument (typed-replay + carriage-return does not submit in claude-code or codex), (B) baseline pre-existing expected-output files so the FileWatcher completion path does not fire on stale outputs from a previous run. Both in protected blocks/ai."
    }
  ],
